post_text:
Dear CR Family and Students,

Most of our K-2 and Blue Team students/families coming to school on Monday and Tuesday have received their bus pickup times for tomorrow. Those coming to school on Thursday and Friday will receive bus pickup times on Wednesday.

If you did not receive bus pickup times, here are some ranges that will help our families. We apologize if we were not able to connect with you.

Families in the northern part of our district (example - Caneadea, Centerville, Rushford) the bus will be through between 7am - 7:35am.

Families in the southern part of our district (example - Cuba, West Clarksville, Black Creek) the bus will be through between 7:10am - 7:45am.

Bus pickup times will be affected by the fact that each student is having their temperature checked. Until we go through this cycle a couple of times, please expect some changes in time the first week.

We thank all of you for your patience and we learn and adjust.

Carlos Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
I am happy to share that Cuba-Rushford, through an application process, received the CEP Grant (Community Eligibility Provision) which allows us to serve all students FREE breakfast & Lunch throughout the year.

I want to thank Mr. Alex Leyva for his determination in working through this grant as we started this process back on April 1, 2020. We were anxiously waiting and hoping for good news!

As we start the year, we will still be sending out forms for income verification as we have done in the past. One of the big factors in receiving the grant is proving your district is above the 40% Free and Reduced level. We barely made it over, so we need your help in September to keep qualifying. More information will be forthcoming.

So Happy for our families!

Carlos Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Homeschooling vs Online Schooling:

This week I was asked to clarify the difference between the two. See Below.

In homeschooling, parents act as full-time instructors. If choosing to homeschool, all school requirements are the full responsibility of the parent/guardian. Homeschooling can only take place once 'Homeschooling Plans' have been submitted to the superintendent for approval and the course of study/curriculum submitted is equivalent in nature to the instruction the student would otherwise receive in school. In online schooling — known at CR as Virtual Academy— online teachers manage the student's studies remotely within a structured curriculum provided by the school. Students in Virtual Academy are held to CR Code of Conduct and attendance policies. If you are requesting CR's Virtual Academy, please submit your request by August 14th.

Carlos Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Dear Cuba-Rushford Community,

In early June, the administration had conversations regarding the possible controversy of our mascot, Cuba-Rushford Rebels. At that time, it was decided the conversations about a change would be brought to the Board of Education. While this is not part of our July public meeting, suggestions have been presented to the Board of Education. Opportunity for community voice in regard to a possible change in mascot will be forthcoming.
Because conversations are under way and no decisions have been made, there is no need for a formal petition at this time. We appreciate your enthusiasm and support of the Cuba-Rushford School District and look forward to positive and productive conversations on this topic.

Carlos Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools

The Graduation Committee will be meeting to reengineer graduation now that Governor Cuomo announced that outdoor, socially-distancing graduations of up to 150 people will be allowed.

The district will revert back to its current plan should the executive order revert back to a more restrictive setting due to any outbreaks or significant changes.

Thank you very much!

Carlos Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Dear Cuba Rushford Community and Parents,

I want to thank those parents who reached out to me directly with the concerns of Cross Country not being offered for 1 year as a cost saving measure. I am always available and willing to be transparent with any decision or question asked.
One of our board members suggested we proceed with Cross Country sign-ups to gauge the level of participation and interest in the sport￼￼￼￼￼￼￼. We currently have 4 students for the 20-21 school year. I have asked Mr. Cappelletti to please put out signups for Cross Country.
The district will be forming an athletic committee in a couple of weeks once public school districts have a better understanding of what re-opening looks like. We want to make sure everyone has a voice.
Thank you for your patience and reaching out to me directly.

Mr. Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Attention Class of 2020 and Senior Families:
Yesterday Governor Cuomo announced that schools will remain closed through the end of the school year. This is sad for all of us, but especially for you.
We want you to know that we are working to make this an extra special year for you. We have plans in the works and announcements coming.
By now you have received information about Step 1 in our Senior Celebration: Cap and Gown Pictures - Friday, May 8th. Please confirm your time if you have not already.

Cuba-Rushford community, watch for our announcements and be ready to celebrate our seniors! We appreciate your care, concern, and Rebel pride!

post_text:
Hello again!!
In the past, it has been offered to pay for a “senior ad” in the yearbook for your graduating senior. You’d be able to write a short message, wishing your child good luck or whatever you’d like. We are doing that again, but for free. However, the deadline to have the book done is quickly approaching, so Grace Stolberg needs your requests by Thursday (April 23rd) morning. Text or Facebook message me with any questions and what you’d like to write in the yearbook! Thank you! (585)968-2178

The 2020 Census is LIVE! Most households should have received their first mailing from the Census Bureau between March 12th and March 20th.

https://www.census.gov/newsroom/press-kits/2020/2020-census-mailings.html

The 2020 Census online and phone systems are now Live. Online access to the 2020 Census form can be found at my2020census.gov and the phone response option can be reached at 1-844-330-2020 (TDD service for the hearing impaired can be reached at 1-844-467-2020). The Census Bureau has released a Video Guide demonstrating how to navigate the online 2020 Census form from start to finish. Language guides for 59 non-English languages can be found at Language Guides (Print), including a Large Print guide.

A few updates for the Rebel Nation.

The Cuba-Rushford Central School District is working on a plan to increase outside wifi capabilities near their school buildings. We are also looking to create wifi hotspots in a few targeted areas. We will continue to post updates as this plan develops.

The Districts breakfast and lunch handout plan going well. We encourage all students who have not taken advantage of this yet to please join us as we have plenty of resources for those in need.

The Cuba-Rushford Capital Project has not been halted during the districts closer and work continues to stay on schedule. For updates and video of these improvements check out today’s Rebel Express Show.

Carlos Gildemeister

post_text:
Child Care Resource and Referral Agencies (CCRRs) provide services to parents and day care providers in every county of New York State.

If you are looking for child care, the CCRR in our county is a great place to start. They will ask you about the kind of care you are looking for, the ages of your children, the hours of care you need and other specifics such as any special needs your child might have. Based on that information, they will be able to give you a list of providers that most closely meet your needs.

https://ocfs.ny.gov/main/childcare/referralagencies.asp

Dear Parents, Students and Community Members,

Late this morning I will be meeting with all Allegany and Cattaraugus Superintendents followed by a meeting with all the principals, managers, and other key members this afternoon to hammer out final details. I will be sending out a message between 3 - 5 pm with final details to our families and community memebers.

The district will be providing meals to our students commencing Wednesday 17th, 2020 until this crisis is over. Details to follow.

I appreciate your patience and understanding in the interim.

Carlos Gildemeister

Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Attention Rebels Athletes! Casey Kacz will be a guest speaker this Friday August 23rd. He will be focusing on how to be a great athlete, teammate and experience success by practicing humility, service and right attitude. Girls @ 8:30am and Boys @ 9:55am in the MHS Aud. #mycrcs

Casey is a native of Amherst, NY. He attended Sweet Home High School (‘09) where he quarterbacked the Panthers to their first State Championship. Attended Buffalo State College (‘13) where he served as a two time captain on the football team and majored in Health and Wellness. He went on to play two seasons of Arena Football in 2015 and 2016 for the Columbus Lions and Cleveland Gladiators. Casey started part time at Cross Training Athletics in 2008 and has been full time for the last 3 years. CTA is a non profit organization specializing in character education and leadership training. He and his wife Kelsey live in Tonawanda, NY.

*** Public Service Announcement ***

This morning some ammunition in the form of two bullets were found in the walkway of the middle/ high school. The district took necessary precautions to ensure all students were safe. The Cuba Police Department in conjunction with the New York State Police and other law enforcement agencies swept the building to ensure there were no weapons or other items within the schools. Police K-9 units were utilized and a public information officer was assigned to the entrance of the school campus to ensure no unnecessary visitors were let in as well has to keep parents and stakeholders abreast of the situation. Several officers were posted at our other campus locations to reassure parents and staff as well as students that they had adequate security. Upon thorough investigation it was determined that there was no active threat. All campuses have resumed normal activities and all are safe at this time.

We appreciate everyone’s cooperation and help.

Carlos Gildemeister - Superintendent of Schools
Dustin Burch - Cuba Chief of Police

Dear Cuba-Rushford Middle High Parents. Today, Tuesday October 24th at 9:09am, the district conducted a 'Lock-down Drill' as part of NYS Safe Schools Statute.

The statute now requires twelve drills be conducted each school year, four of which must be lock-down drills, the remaining eight are required to be evacuation drills as in the past.

Please use this opportunity to talk to your children about the importance of looking and listening to the adult supervising them for instructions. The district takes safety very seriously and appreciates the trust you place on us while your child is learning with us.

#Mycrcs #safeschools

Universal Pre-Kindergarten Registration at Cuba-Rushford Elementary

If you would like to register your child for our 2017-2018 Universal Pre-Kindergarten programs, please complete the form and return ASAP to:

Ms. Nicole Deck
Cuba-Rushford Elementary School
15 Elm Street
Cuba, NY 14727
585-968-1760 ext. 0

Preschool Information:
• Cuba-Rushford Elementary will be offering morning and afternoon sessions during the 2017-2018 school year. The morning class begins at 8 a.m. and ends at 10:30 a.m. The afternoon class begins at 12 noon and ends at 2:30 p.m.
• No transportation is provided.

Cuba-Rushford Elementary School also has a Head Start program. About 90% of our students arrive at kindergarten having had a positive Pre-K experience. Research shows that a quality Pre-K experience has a long lasting positive impact on students’ overall success and achievement.

Important mailings about pre-kindergarten registration and screening will be sent to the address below in April.

Please call 585-968-1760 x 0 to sign up your student.

post_text: The Cuba-Rushford junior division Scholastic Challenge team comprised of Claire Benham, Ali Barnes, Hailey Kumpf, Summer Mattison, and Christianna Reynolds won the competition held at Portville Central School on Saturday February 4. They were the lone undefeated team in the 14-team junior division. In the finals, Cuba-Rushford defeated the Scio Junior Tigers. The C-R team displayed a great deal of poise, focus, and teamwork during the event to win the championship. Cuba-Rushford wants to thank all the BOCES personnel and other volunteers who put in so much of their time to make this day a positive and rewarding experience for all of the area students involved. #mycrcs

Parent Information Session

A parent informational session will be held on Friday, February 3rd in the evening at 6:30 p.m. in the MS/HS library. During the parent session, I will review the circumstances that led to the lock down, how the lock down was initiated, and steps we are taking to move forward. Parents will have an opportunity to provide feedback and ask questions about District procedures and the steps we took, and will take, to maintain a safe school environment.

Carlos Gildemeister
Superintendent of Schools
